{
  "text": "A \u202b\u05df5\u202c coverage BAC genomic library, with an average insert size of 130 kb, was constructed for the bichir (P. senegalus) as described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). High-density 5 \u202b\u05df\u202c 5 arrayed filters were made by the RZPD (http:// www.rzpd.de). Hybridization using nonradioactive DIG-labeled probes was done following methods described in [CITATION_3] . The first screen of this library was carried out using a pool of bichir (gift of C. Ledje and F. Ruddle; [CITATION_4] and coelacanth (gift of T. Powers [Benaroya Research Institute at Virginia Mason, Seattle, WA] and C. Amemiya) homeobox sequences isolated in genome-wide PCR surveys. This screen identified nine BAC clones of P. senegalus. A PCR survey of each BAC clone was done using a degenerate homeobox primer pair (334, 5\u0408-GARYTIGARAARGARTTY-3\u0408; 335, 5\u0408-ICKICKRTTYT GRAACAA-3\u0408). One clone containing the posterior part of the HoxA (Evx1, HoxA13, HoxA11, HoxA10) cluster was identified. Bichir HoxB, HoxC, and HoxD cluster sequences are presently being analyzed (C.-H. Chiu, K. Dewar, and P.F. Stadler, unpubl.) .",
